===Ratings===
Scaly Adventures is aired through the Daystar television network on several channels, including Liberty University's Liberty Channel <ref>{{cite web|title=Liberty Channel|url=http://www.liberty.edu/libertychannel/index.cfm?PID=29612|website=Liberty University|publisher=Liberty University|accessdate=23 June 2014}}</ref> and KCHFTV.<ref>{{cite web|title=Scaly Adventures|url=http://kchftv.org/scaly-adventures/|website=KCHFTV|accessdate=14 November 2014}}</ref> Daystar is not currently rated by Nielson.

==Promotional activities==
The Currens have been featured through several news outlets, including the Marietta Daily Journal<ref>{{cite web|last1=Westwood|first1=Sarah|title=Marietta K-9 unit to be featured on TV show|url=http://mdjonline.com/view/full_story/25278345/article-Marietta-K-9-unit-to-be-featured-on-TV-show--?instance=home_lead_story|website=The Marietta Daily Journal|publisher=Marietta Daily Journal|accessdate=24 June 2014}}</ref> and WSPA Channel 7 News.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Coates|first1=Shelby|title=Pickens Co. Family Promoting Snake Safety This Summer|url=http://www.wspa.com/story/25696446/pickens-co-family-promoting-snake-safety-this-summer|website=wspa.com|publisher=Media General Communication Holdings, LLC.|accessdate=23 June 2014}}</ref>  The family also serves as partners in education with their alma mater, Kennesaw State University.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Westwood|first1=Sarah|title=Marietta K-9 unit to be featured on TV show|url=https://web.kennesaw.edu/news/stories/marietta-k-9-unit-be-featured-tv-show-read-more-marietta-daily-journal-marietta-k-9-unit-be-|website=News at KSU|publisher=Kennesaw State University|accessdate=24 June 2014}}</ref>

